description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Practitioners - Anaesthetics/Scrub&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Division: Planned Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care Group: Peri-Operative &amp; Critical Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band: 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: £24,907 - £30,615 per annum/pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: Tuesday 1st December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting for &lt;strong&gt;Theatre Practitioners/Anaesthetic Assistants - Operating Department Practitioners or Anaesthetic Nurses &lt;/strong&gt;who shares our ambition and vision to deliver the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Best of Care by the Best People&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and has the drive to take us forward, by ensuring that the Trust continues to be the first choice for patients and our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will have opportunities to work in Scrub and Anaesthetics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to offer excellent development opportunities in a wide range of specialties including General Surgery, Emergency, Orthopaedics, Trauma, Gynaecology, Urology and Obstetrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Operating Department Practitioners (or due to qualify) and Nurses with an Anaesthetic qualification who are keen to maintain and/or develop skills as Anaesthetic Assistant. Previous experience would be an advantage but full training and support will be given to newly qualified ODP’s and nurses with an anaesthetic qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by a mentor who will be able to offer support and assist with further development, and you will have the opportunity to rotate between scrub, recovery and anaesthetics if you so wish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will have excellent communication skills, be able to work well in a team and provide high quality patient centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust and its employees are all committed to creating and maintaining a fair and supportive working environment and culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our commitment to you, we will give you the opportunity to utilise and enhance your talents to assist us in the development of shaping the future of Medway NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust offers a number of apprenticeships and training opportunities in Leadership and Management, Business Services, Finance, Accounting, Human Resources, Clinical Support Work, Research and Innovation, Nursing Associate and Assistant Practitioner alongside our in-house comprehensive clinical pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our hope is that our education pathways will play a key role in enabling you to challenge the practices of the past and build capability for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to the protection of children, young people, their families and vulnerable adults accessing its services. Promoting the message that “safeguarding is everyone’s business” is vital to ensure our patients are protected and safe from abuse. To this end you must comply with Trust’s and the Kent and Medway Safeguarding Board’s policies on safeguarding children, young people and vulnerable adults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values are &lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;old, &lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;very Person Counts, &lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt;haring and Open and &lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;ogether.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To contribute to our exciting future and become part of our team, apply today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJess HarmanJob titlePractice Development NurseEmail addressjessica.harman@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
